content: That's a great question! I've recently had a lifer experience with a yellow warbler, and I'm still thrilled about it. I've been wanting to see one for a while, and it was amazing to finally tick it off my list. But I think I'd like to learn more about the common yellowthroat. I've seen them a few times, but I'm not always confident in my identification. I've heard they can be tricky to distinguish from other warblers, especially during the fall migration.
